replies.bodyText:
It was there to explain why the if/else if/else.  The only reason for them is to generate suffices.  If I didn't care about having unique suffices, I would just do a simple
return separatedBySuicide.stream()
        .map(newFiringUnits -> new FiringGroup(name, newFiringUnits, targetUnits))
        .collect(Collectors.toList());

But I've been thinking about your comments here and I think if I instead change the above to:
return separatedBySuicide.stream()
        .map(newFiringUnits -> new FiringGroup(generateName(name, newFiringUnits, separatedBySuicide), newFiringUnits, targetUnits))
        .collect(Collectors.toList());

Then the logic for the unique names is more obviously contained to just dealing with the string instead of generating firing groups.

